library(sf)
## Linking to GEOS 3.8.1, GDAL 3.1.1, PROJ 6.3.1
library(readr)
library(elevatr)
library(raster)
## Loading required package: sp
## 
## Attaching package: 'raster'
## The following object is masked from 'package:dplyr':
## 
##     select
## The following object is masked from 'package:tidyr':
## 
##     extract
goleta = readr::read_csv("data/uscities.csv") %>%
  st_as_sf(coords = c("lng", "lat"), crs = 4326) %>%
  st_transform(5070) %>%
  filter(city == "Goleta") %>%
  st_buffer(5000)
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   city = col_character(),
##   city_ascii = col_character(),
##   state_id = col_character(),
##   state_name = col_character(),
##   county_fips = col_double(),
##   county_name = col_character(),
##   county_fips_all = col_character(),
##   county_name_all = col_character(),
##   lat = col_double(),
##   lng = col_double(),
##   population = col_double(),
##   density = col_double(),
##   source = col_character(),
##   military = col_logical(),
##   incorporated = col_logical(),
##   timezone = col_character(),
##   ranking = col_double(),
##   zips = col_character(),
##   id = col_double()
## )
bb = goleta %>%
  st_bbox() %>%
  st_as_sfc() %>%
  st_as_sf() %>%
  elevatr::get_elev_raster(z = 13) 
## Warning in sp::proj4string(locations): CRS object has comment, which is lost in
## output

## Warning in sp::proj4string(locations): CRS object has comment, which is lost in
## output

## Warning in sp::proj4string(locations): CRS object has comment, which is lost in
## output
## Mosaicing & Projecting
## Note: Elevation units are in meters.
## Note: The coordinate reference system is:
##  +proj=aea +lat_0=23 +lon_0=-96 +lat_1=29.5 +lat_2=45.5 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs
ele = crop(bb, goleta)

goleta_ele = plot(ele, main="Elevation of Goleta")

raster(ele)
